                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"S=\sum_{n=0}^{ \infty } \dfrac{(-1)^n n}{ 2016^n }=-\left(\frac{1}{2016}+\frac{3}{2016^3}+\frac{5}{2016^5}+\cdots\right)+\left(\frac{2}{2016^2}+\frac{4}{2016^4}+\frac{6}{2016^6}+\cdots\right)"}],"attrs":{"inline":false}},{"type":"text","text":" Clearly, this is the sum of two Arithmetic-Geometric Progressions, which are easily evaluated, giving us the answer -2019."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

